# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) to override the API origin for `npm run dev` / `npm run build`.
# Vite only exposes variables prefixed with `VITE_` to client code.
#
# Default dev uses `.env.development`: `VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api`. The Vite dev server proxies `/api/*`
# to the backend (see `vite.config.ts`). Without that proxy, `/api/*` is answered by the SPA and
# `response.json()` fails with "Unexpected token '<'".
#
# Docker Compose publishes the API on the host at port 8010 by default; the proxy targets
# `http://127.0.0.1:8010`. Override in `.env.local` (applies to dev + preview) if the API runs
# elsewhere — for example bare uvicorn on port 8000:
# GRAPHCLERK_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8000
#
# Or bypass the proxy (browser calls the API directly; CORS must allow the UI origin):
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8010
